**Explanation:**
The `debounce` function delays the execution of a provided function until after a certain amount of time has elapsed since the last time the debounced function was invoked.

```javascript
// Debounce function
function debounce(func, delay) {
  let timeoutId;
  return function (...args) {
    const context = this;
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);
    timeoutId = setTimeout(() => func.apply(context, args), delay);
  };
}

// Example usage:
const heavyFunction = () => {
  console.log('Heavy function executed');
};

const debouncedHeavyFunction = debounce(heavyFunction, 300); // Debounced function with a delay of 300ms

// Simulate multiple function invocations in a short period
debouncedHeavyFunction();
debouncedHeavyFunction();
debouncedHeavyFunction();

// After a 300ms delay, "Heavy function executed" will be logged only once
```
